{
  "stem": "23155.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She was there conducting the band, and we were marching into this.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I don't remember what they were playing, but they were playing a marching song, and we  marched in.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The inmates of the women's camp didn't like us very much.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After all, we had hair.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they knew that we are going to be moved out from Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because still then, nobody left Auschwitz unless you escaped somehow, like one of our prisoners did with the help of one SS man, which I will relate to you now.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As I told you, we went out to pick the stones.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they used to come with us, SS men, and also some prisoners, some men prisoners.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The SS man was by the name of Pistek.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was a Romanian of German origin.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And as we were picking those stones to take them with us, I saw them pointing at different places and talking.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I said to myself, there's something fishy going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sure enough, the next day the sirens went, and the sirens meant that somebody escaped.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, this SS man took this prisoner and gave him a uniform, and they-- he had arranged with a farmer to give him a-- a bicycle.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And what did he do?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He went back to Theresienstadt, and he told people that they shouldn't go in the transport, what-- and told them what awaits them.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they didn't believe him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] So now I'm going back to [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't-- the prisoners, there were a lot of young Slovak-- I mean Jewish girls from Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I-- you know, people don't know here that in Slovakia they had SS, but they were Slovaks.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
